# REST API Best Practices

## Resource & Verbs

- **Nouns, plural**: `/users`, `/subscriptions`, `/token-packages`
- **HTTP verbs**: GET (read), POST (create), PUT/PATCH (update), DELETE (delete)
- **Nested resources** when ownership is clear: `/users/{id}/subscriptions`

## Status Codes

| Code | Use |
|------|-----|
| 200 | Success (GET, PATCH) |
| 201 | Created (POST) |
| 204 | No content (DELETE) |
| 400 | Bad request (malformed input) |
| 401 | Unauthorized (missing/invalid auth) |
| 403 | Forbidden (lacks permission) |
| 404 | Not found |
| 409 | Conflict (duplicate, precondition failed) |
| 422 | Unprocessable (validation errors) |
| 429 | Too many requests (rate limit) |
| 500 | Internal server error (never leak internals) |

## Design Rules

- **Versioning**: Prefix with `/v1/`, `/v2/` for future compatibility
- **Idempotency**: `Idempotency-Key` header for POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE
- **Pagination**: Cursor-based or `?limit=&offset=` for list endpoints
- **Errors**: Consistent JSON `{ "code": "...", "message": "...", "details": {...} }`; never expose stack traces
- **Validation**: Validate all inputs; return 400/422 with field-level errors
- **Request/response size limits**; document max payload sizes
- **Deprecation**: `Sunset` and `Deprecation` headers when retiring endpoints
